profile:
Valentini Kitchens has been building and renovating Quality Kitchens and Cabinetry since 1974 to the Toronto and surrounding GTA markets. 
Valentini Kitchens is a true "Family Business" that has been owned and operated by the Pasquariello Family for over 45 years. 
Valentini was founded in 1974 by the late Mike Pasquariello and is now run by his 3 sons, Tony, Piero and Marco. 
We at Valentini Kitchens have maintained a high quality standard and reputation from our first day in business, with our attention to detail and service to our customer as our # 1 motive.
 
Today, we have made changes to our business to compete with our changing markets and with our changes we will maintain our quality and service to make sure our clients are 100% satisfied. We have also implemented a few more cost effective lines of Cabinetry, many that are locally sourced and a few off shore lines to meet the changing markets and cost budgets of our clientele.
 
Valentini Kitchens offers Cabinetry in many options to fit your needs and budget:
- Full custom made line of Kitchen, Bath and various types of Cabinetry and Mill Work.
- Semi custom made locally sourced and branded line of Kitchen, Bath, Laundry & Closet Cabinetry.
- Semi custom made off shore sourced and branded line of Kitchen and Bath Cabinetry.

  
Full line of custom made Residential Cabinetry Options including: 
- Kitchens and Bath Cabinetry
- TV, Entertainment and Wall Unit Cabinetry
- Bar and Built In Cabinetry
- Laundry & Mud Room Cabinetry
- Home Office Cabinetry
- Closet Organizers and Home Storage Solutions



Full line of custom made Commercial / Industrial Cabinetry Options including:
- Office Kitchen & Bath Cabinetry 
- Custom Cabinetry for Restaurants, Bars, Coffee Houses, Hair Salon / Spas, Dental and Doctor Offices, etc.

 
When you purchase a service from Valentini, you are buying into a family that has a reputation of giving our customers 100% of Quality, Service and most importantly Price.
Being one of a handful of the GTA'S Cabinetry Pioneers, Valentini is small in size but is evolving with the everyday changes in the world of Woodworking and Full Home Renovations.
Valentini offers a true complete "1 Stop" shopping experience by providing customers with full Renovation capabilities. We can start with an in home or in showroom consultation and the rest is up to the customer. Valentini can take care of full project management from start to completion. We offer a full range of Renovations to complete selection of Retail Products.
What makes us at Valentini Kitchens Unique is that we are one of the only companies that allows consumers to purchase everything directly from us for use on their Home Renovations, meaning "We Install Everything We Sell". By supplying the retail products we sell, we can insure you as the home owner full warranties of the products we use on the job and also "Less Time" having to run around to have all the products ready on the job site. We take care of showing you the products in our own Kitchens and Bath Showroom and the delivery of everything to your home when it is needed for the Renovation.

 
Valentini also offers a full list of Retail Showroom Products including: 
- Premade Bath Vanity Cabinetry
- Tile, Stone and Mosaics
- Hardwood, Vinyl, Laminate and Carpet Flooring
- Quartz, Granite, Marble and Laminate Counter Tops
- Plumbing Fixtures
 



As many companies grow in size, we at Valentini Kitchens want to remain small in size with our 1 Factory Showroom Location, we pride ourselves in maintaining our high standards of Quality, Service and Reputation that has made is one of the leaders in the Kitchen and Renovation Industry for over 4 decades. As a family business, we offer the ultimate hands on approach with any project we take on.

Valentini offers a 1 hour "In home" or "In Showroom" free Estimate Consultation (By Appointment only).
Please Call or Email us with your inquiries today. (Please leave a voice mail message or email us if we are not able to respond the same day as we may be on the job site, We will definitely respond back to everyone that contacts us as soon as possible ). 

Valentini Kitchens and the Pasquariello Family had its own hot reality TV series called "Building Family" in 2005 on HGTV Canada. This series aired weekly nationwide with a total of 6 half hour episodes. Please click here on the Homestars Valentini Kitchens Video Galleries to watch the episodes and to read up more on this, please visit our website. 
 
We hope all of our past and future customers enjoy watching this show as it shows the everyday life of our family business working together in the real world of Kitchen Manufacturing and Home Renovations with a flare of true reality in our day to day activities.

profile: As a family owned and operated business, The Marble Clinic has over 30 years experience in the field of natural stone protection and restoration - and with that experience our highly knowledgeable staff is able to provide the best outcome for your natural stone. Specializing in the fields of protection, restoration as well as maintenance. Each project has individual needs and The Marble Clinics team of experts work to produce top quality results. We offer the following services: Marble Cleaning: Remove dirt and dust stuck in the stone surface or in the grout lines this will not remove scratches or etching alone. Wax Stripping: The use of wax and topical coatings can damage natural stone over time, and causes yellowing after short periods of heavy traffic; The Marble Clinic can remove topical coatings from any natural stone to prepare it for proper restoration and sealing techniques. Stone Grinding: This is the most common restoration technique and will remove deep scratches, lippage, etching, white stun marks and yellowing. It is also used to remove epoxy from chip and crack repairs. Marble Polishing: Through mechanical polishing methods, natural stone acquires a high lustre and reflects natural light it therefore does not need topical coatings or wax to achieve a desired shine. Marble Honing: Will remove minor etching on low lustre stone surfaces, and give the surface a clean uniform finish without the polished look. Finish Alteration: The Marble Clinic can change the appearance of a natural stones finish; from honed to polished, polished to honed, and everything in-between. Countertop Seam-Polishing: Visible counter top seams can be filled with epoxy based resins, ground and polished or honed to match the stone colour and virtually disappear. Chip and Crack Repair: Chips and cracks in any natural stone can be filled with coloured epoxy resin and refinished to match the surrounding material. Grout Cleaning and Sealing: Over time grout accumulates dirt and becomes quite dirty. Grout can be cleaned and sealed to improve the floors beauty and facilitate easier maintenance cleaning. Grout Colouring: An easy way to change the look and feel of a tile floor. Stone Sealing: All natural stone should be professionally cleaned and sealed to increase the longevity of the material and repel dark staining solutions. Colour Enhancing: Using enhancing impregnators on flamed or textured material is an excellent way to protect your stone and bring it back to life. Table Repair: Our expert technicians can repair most tables, mantals, fireplaces, statues or fountains so long as it is a relatively clean break. Stone Maintenance: Specially formulated compounds used on an annual or semi-annual basis keep any surface in high traffic areas looking good year round.

profile: Siding, Stucco, Stone, Brick, Masonry and Fireplaces From design to installation, Stone Selex Design is a premier company with over 20 years of experience providing both residential and commercial customers with quality installation and a high level of customer satisfaction. Stone Selex Design is committed to providing full service installation for your exterior or interior stone veneer project. We also provide installation of stone veneer, stucco, brick, masonry and fireplace transformations. Design your own project with the NEW Stone Veneer Visualizer and have Stone Selex Design install it for you. The Visualizer gives you the ability to envision your project from the comfort of your computer screen. It has the power to transform a photo of your home into a professional digital rendering by adding siding, stucco and stone. Make your home the talk of the neighbourhood with stone and stucco, or stone and brick, or siding and brick, stone tile and wood siding. The possibilities of style and colour combinations are endless. A Stone Selex Design project manager will help you with each stage of your project from where to add stone, stucco, siding, brick and masonry and provide you with a quote for our installation services provided by our experienced masonry installers. If its a fireplace that you want to create or just simply add stone or masonry, Stone Selex Design and the visualizer can help you with this too. While you are in the planning stages of your fireplaces transformation the visualizer is a great tool to use. Look through photos for ideas and see what others are doing and then come to Stone Selex Design and ask us to install it for you. Visit us here: https://twitter.com/StoneSelex https://www.facebook.com/StoneSelexInc/

Natural stone is an ideal decoration for those who appreciate classic beauty and references to nature in interior design. Whats more, it is a very universal material that will work both in interiors  e.g. as a kitchen or living room decoration, but also outside  as a facade or fence covering.

Renovation
Bathroom finishing is a very important and at the same time the basic element of any major renovation or interior finishing. profile:
With 10 years of experience and excellent customer service Art Express Tiles has made its brand well recognized. We have brought customer satisfaction and quality work to every home in the city. Our business model is dedicated to bring your vision of new kitchen, bathroom, office floor real. Ask our customers, check our work and see for yourself.

The professional team at Art Express Tiles Installation has been dedicated to quality tile craftsmanship and customer satisfaction for over 10 years. Our philosophy is simple: integrity is the foundation of every project. Art Express Tiles developed a comprehensive guideline applied to each project incorporating our high standards and measures of quality. Whether an multi-storied office facility or a minor home renovation, we employ the same guidelines for value management, scheduling, budgeting and coordination. We follow-up extensively to ensure a successfully completed project every time.

We are a WSIB Ontario insured and bonded company. Click here to read more about the services we offer.
services:
No matter if youre looking for marble, porcelain or granite tile installations, our professional tile installers and marble setters have the quality supplies and unsurpassed expertise to match your tiling needs. We use various suppliers to provide you with multiple tile choices at prices that wont exceed your budget.

Our process of accessing and quoting a job allows us to inform you and be proactive to any issues that could arise. We also discuss in detail what your vision and ideas are as well as the functionality of the space. We can offer our insight to using different tiles like Porcelain, Natural Stone, Marble or Granite etc. We also offer tips how to maintain and prolong the life of your home renovation investment.

We take our time to examine the project area and let you know what the work entails. We explain to you our pricing which usually depends on, labour hours needed, square footage, tile material, size of the tile. Also, different tile cutters and leveling techniques can take more time. We discuss your renovation ideas, color-scheme, and the upkeep of your choice. We also explain and communicate the details of each step of your project.

Throughout the installation of the project, we keep the communication open to answer all of your questions. Take a look at some of our testimonials to see what our clients have to say about the quality of work and customer service we provide!

Contact us today for a FREE quote and to discuss your tiling project.

profile:
Araujo Concrete Floor Inc. specializes in concrete floors - dry pack (cement tile) and tile. 
In 2000, HW Araujo was established and in July 2011, we became incorporated as Araujo Concrete Floor Inc. 
After 20 years experience, mostly in Ontario, we have grown and decided to expand into preparing subfloor, and professional tile installation. 
We feel that it is most beneficial to the customer having one company providing complete services from start to finish.

We prepare and finish subfloors of any kind, making them ready to receive marble, wood, granite, tile, carpet ... etc. 
After the subfloor has been smoothed, leveled and sloped, we lay the tile, avoiding any lippage and providing a beautiful seamless surface.

We have worked with several builders in the Toronto, Calgary, London, Hamilton, Oakville, Mississauga, Oshawa, Cambridge, and Halifax areas, among many others. 
We work with a number of different contractors, including Kenaidan, Baycon Construction, Upper Deck Flooring, Zet Master and many more.

We pride ourselves in having done all the dry pack floors in Apple Stores throughout Canada with the DC Marble and Granite Company. 
Other high profile dry pack projects we have worked on include Pearson International Airport, Ripley Aquarium, Bank of Montreal and Louis Vuitton. 
In addition to the dry pack installations, we have installed porcelain tile in the Pen Center Mall, Sports Chek, Marks Work Warehouse and many more custom commercial and residential sites.

We look forward to servicing you for all your flooring needs.
